title: error: internal compiler error: encountered incremental compilation error with exported_symbols(core[96cd])

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code I tried compiling the post-03 branch of blog os with cg_clif to test inline assembly support @nbdd0121 implemented in https://github.com/bjorn3/rustc_codegen_cranelift/pull/1206. For this I did `RUSTC="/path/to/cg_clif" cargo bootimage`. This didn't work due to a bug introduced by me in cg_clif. To workaround it, I tried `RUSTFLAGS="-Ccodegen-units=1" RUSTC="/path/to/cg_clif" cargo bootimage`. This resulted in an unstable fingerprint ICE. ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.58.0-nightly (d914f17ca 2021-11-16) binary: rustc commit-hash: d914f17ca71a33a89b2dc3436fca51b1a091559e commit-date: 2021-11-16 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.58.0-nightly LLVM version: 13.0.0 ``` ### Error output
